    "value": "**4. Write crash/land logic**"
  },
  {
    "kind": 2,
    "language": "javascript",
    "value": "let gameIsRunning = true;\r\nlet crashVelocityThreshold = 3;\r\n\r\nfunction checkCollision(){\r\n    if(ship.altitude > 405){        \r\n        if(ship.velocity > crashVelocityThreshold){\r\n            // Speed would be too high at contact [CRASH]\r\n            gameIsRunning = false; // For now, for debug purposes you can still take off after a successful landing                    \r\n        }else{\r\n            // Speed would be safe for contact [LAND]\r\n        }\r\n        ship.altitude = 405;\r\n        ship.velocity = 0;\r\n        ship.acceleration = 0;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction draw(){\r\n    if(gameIsRunning){\r\n        drawEnvironment();\r\n        applyGravity();\r\n        accelerateShip();\r\n        checkCollision();\r\n        drawShip(ship.latitude, ship.altitude);\r\n    }\r\n}"
  },
